warning[PG003]: new exempt path `*::test::*` in `paradigms.CX.exempt_paths`
  --> locus.lock:1
  - exemption silences the rule entirely for matching modules; prefer narrowing the rule via overrides with debt metadata, or fixing the underlying code
  fix: if this is a deliberate calibration, re-run `locus check` with `--allow-policy-calibration`. The exempt-paths schema will gain debt metadata in a follow-up; until then exemptions are visible additions.

warning[PG007]: new exempt path `*::test::*` in `paradigms.CX.exempt_paths` lacks debt metadata (reason, expires, owner)
  --> locus.lock:1
  - an exempt-path silences a rule for matching modules; without `reason` / `expires` / `owner` it becomes invisible debt
  - missing field(s): reason, expires, owner
  - PG007 is unaffected by `--allow-policy-calibration`: calibration accepts the addition itself (PG003), but does not waive the requirement to record why, when to revisit, and who owns it
  fix: populate `reason` (why this exemption exists), `expires` (`YYYY-MM-DD` review date), and `owner` (team/individual). Use the struct form: `{"pattern": "…", "reason": "…", "expires": "YYYY-MM-DD", "owner": "…"}`.

